## 4. Products & Services

- **Detailed descriptions:** Roll-off dumpster rental and hauling. Containers are delivered to and removed from job sites for three primary use cases — new construction, renovation/remodel projects, and residential/commercial property clean-outs. The business operates multiple roll-off trucks and a container fleet of ~186 dumpsters.
- **Pricing model:** Per-rental / per-haul, typically priced by container size, debris type, rental duration, and distance. Orlando-market roll-off pricing in 2026 runs roughly $300–$800 per rental (10–40 yard). Revenue is transactional, not contracted — though repeat-customer behavior is very high. Growth path explicitly includes raising prices.
- **Competitive differentiators:** ~26-year local tenure and brand; a ~100% gross-profit service model (the listing's framing — i.e., labor-and-asset-driven service with minimal cost of goods); modern dispatch software enabling lean operations; a referral engine (95% of new clients) that holds CAC near zero; an owned container fleet (~186 units) that is a barrier to entry for new operators.

