## 9. Risk Factors

- **Industry-specific risks:** Construction-cycle exposure — a slowdown in Orlando starts would hit volume directly. Landfill tipping-fee inflation is a structural margin headwind in 2026.
- **Financial risks:** EBITDA undisclosed — the headline 3.47x is an SDE multiple and flatters the deal; true EBITDA-basis multiple is est. ~5x. Only one year of financials disclosed — no demonstrated growth trend, so the Buy Box growth criterion cannot be verified. Customer concentration not disclosed.
- **Operational risks:** Lean ~6-person team — loss of one or two experienced drivers is material. The owner is the de facto manager with no GM layer; a management-transition plan is needed even though field ops do not depend on the owner.
- **Regulatory / legal:** Solid-waste hauling requires local/county franchise or permit compliance and FMCSA/DOT registration for trucks and drivers. Confirm Orange County and City of Orlando hauling permits transfer cleanly.
- **Deal-specific conditions:**
  - **Negotiate the $541,000 inventory carve-out into the purchase price** — or discount the equity value accordingly; the $849K ask is misleading without it.
  - **Negotiate to ≤4.0x true EBITDA** — once EBITDA is confirmed, the effective price likely needs to come down from the implied ~5x.
  - **Obtain 3 years of P&Ls and tax returns** to verify the growth criterion before advancing.
  - **Confirm customer concentration** — request top-5 / top-10 customer revenue share.
  - **Verify FTE count and driver tenure/contracts.**

